  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How does HDMI over Fiber work?",
  "response": "HDMI over Fiber works by converting HDMI signals into optical signals that can be transmitted over fiber optic cables. These fiber optic cables use light to carry the data, which allows for high-speed transmission over long distances with minimal signal loss and electromagnetic interference.\n\nHere\u2019s how the process generally works:\n\n1. **Transmitter Unit:** \n   - The HDMI source (such as a Blu-ray player, computer, or game console) connects to the transmitter unit using an HDMI cable.\n   - The transmitter unit converts the HDMI signal into an optical signal.\n\n2. **Fiber Optic Cable:**\n   - The optical signal is sent through the fiber optic cable. Fiber optics are advantageous because they support higher bandwidths, can cover greater distances (up to several kilometers), and are immune to electromagnetic interference.\n\n3. **Receiver Unit:**\n   - At the other end of the fiber optic cable, the receiver unit receives the optical signal.\n   - The receiver unit then converts the optical signal back into an HDMI signal.\n\n4. **HDMI Display:**\n   - The HDMI signal is sent from the receiver unit to the display device (such as a TV, monitor, or projector) via a standard HDMI cable.\n\n**Advantages of HDMI over Fiber:**\n- **Long Distance Transmission:** Fiber optics can transmit signals over much longer distances than traditional HDMI cables, often several kilometers.\n- **High Bandwidth:** Fiber optics support high bandwidth, which is crucial for transmitting high-resolution video formats like 4K and 8K without degradation.\n- **Immunity to Electromagnetic Interference:** Fiber optic cables are not affected by electromagnetic interference, ensuring a stable signal.\n- **Noise Reduction:** Optical signals are less prone to disturbances, providing clearer transmission.\n\n**Applications:**\n- **Commercial Use:** Ideal for large venues, auditoriums, and conference centers where displays and sources are spread out over long distances.\n- **Home Theater Systems:** Useful for complex setups where components are placed in different rooms or locations.\n- **Broadcasting:** In TV studios and live event broadcasting where high-quality signal transmission over long distances is critical.\n\nOverall, HDMI over Fiber is a robust solution for scenarios requiring long-distance, high-quality signal transmission without the drawbacks of traditional HDMI or coaxial cables.",
